# Murali, Kaybitsky District, Republic of Tatarstan

Murali (;  ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Kaybitsky District of the Republic of Tatarstan, Russia, located on the Birlya River,  east of Bolshiye Kaybitsy, the administrative center of the district. Population: 496 (2010 est.); 583 (1997 est.); 611 (1989); all ethnic Tatars. There is a secondary school and a mosque in Murali. The main occupation of the population is agriculture and cattle breeding. Murali has been known to exist since the times of the Khanate of Kazan.
